<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1301,1927]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,321,1781,1807]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is being known as Jarad-al-ushr which means 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1272,1781,1806]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis box="[1046,1272,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Calotropis procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was recorded from Murzuq (Fezzan) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Salfi, M." box="[621,777,1821,1847]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="383 - 388" refId="ref30602" refString="Salfi, M. (1935 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza degli ortotteri libici. 7. Sull Ortotterofauna del Fezzan. (Missione Scortecci della R. Societa geografica Italiana). Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 74, 383 - 388." type="journal article" year="1935">Salfi (1935a)</bibRefCitation>
. It is widely distributed in South of Sahara and the semidesert belt South of it from 
<collectingCountry box="[492,591,1861,1887]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[654,727,1861,1887]" name="Sudan" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[906,976,1861,1887]" name="Egypt" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Egypt</collectingCountry>
to Mauretania and 
<collectingCountry box="[1215,1308,1861,1887]" name="Senegal" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Popov, GB &amp; Kevan, D. K. &amp; MCE" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="8" refId="ref30254" refString="Popov, GB. &amp; Kevan, D. K. MCE. (1979) A revision of the genus Poekilocerus Audinet - Serville 1831 (Orthoptera: Acridoidea: Pyrgomorphidae). Anti-Locust Bulletin, COPR, 8 lpp." type="journal article" year="1979">Popov &amp; Kevan, 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
